// LIGHTHOUSE
	// charles 7 hearts - traumadumping 
	"charleshearts7.0": "*sniff*... Hey, @.",
	"charleshearts7.1": "Sorry, I'm not really good company right now...#Sorry, I'll leave you alone.#That's okay. Can I stand here with you for a bit?",
	"charleshearts7.2": "Yeah, sure. *sniff*.$s",
	"charleshearts7.3": "Do you ever feel like you just can't do things right some days?$s",
	"charleshearts7.4": "Sorry, that was kind of heavy.$s#$b#I just mean, like... it's rough, sometimes, being dead and all.$s#$b#I usually don't mind, not really, because I've got Edwin and I've got the agency and that's all good, you know?#$b#But then I remember how my mates chased me into that lake, or how my dad used to hit me...$s",
	"charleshearts7.5": "Sometimes it's like he's still around, yelling in my ear about how I'm gonna mess this up too.$s#$b#And if I mess up, like, that's it, it's over, you know?...$s#$b#I'd lose Edwin, I'd lose *everything*.$s",
	"charleshearts7.6": "You should focus on the positive things about the present.",
	"charleshearts7.7": "You should try to forget the past.",
	"charleshearts7.8": "It's okay to feel sad sometimes.",
	"charleshearts7.9": "Yeah, you're right. I know I shouldn't worry so much about this sort of thing...",
	"charleshearts7.10": "Yeah, you're right. I know I shouldn't worry so much about this sort of thing...",
	"charleshearts7.11": "Yeah... you sound just like Crystal. I promise I'm trying, alright?",
	"charleshearts7.12": "And it helps making friends like you, don't it?$h#$b#Thanks for listening, @.",
	
// LOST AND FOUND DEPARTMENT
	"NightNurseDebrief.0": "Alright there, @?$9",
	"NightNurseDebrief.1": "Mirror travel can be rough, especially if you're not used to it.$9",
	"NightNurseDebrief.2": "Ahem.",
	"NightNurseDebrief.3": "Have you got a door ready, then?$9",
	"NightNurseDebrief.4": "I really must impress on the both of you how dangerous this is.#$b#To walk willingly into Hell... and with one of you a mortal being, no less!",
	"NightNurseDebrief.5": "I'll be fine. I've done dangerous things before.",
	"NightNurseDebrief.6": "It doesn't matter; Edwin needs our help.",
	"NightNurseDebrief.7": "Do you really need me to go with you, Charles?",
	"NightNurseDebrief.8": "Your silly little escapades in the local caves are nothing compared to the psychological and physical torment of Hell.#$b#But if I cannot stop you...",
	"NightNurseDebrief.9": "Oh, the folly of youth...#$b#You know hardly anything about what you are about to walk into, and yet I suspect it will make no difference in your decision.",
	"NightNurseDebrief.10": "It will be dangerous. I can't ask you to come, and if it were up to me, nobody would ever have to see that place ever again.$9#$b#I've done it alone before, and I'll do it again a thousand times, for Edwin.$9",
	"NightNurseDebrief.11": "Very well. If you are both truly set on this, then follow me.",
	"NightNurseDebrief.12": "The door to Hell is through here.#$b#I shall keep it open while you're gone, but do hurry. The longer it's open, the more danger we are all in.",
	"NightNurseDebrief.13": "I don't have Edwin's map this time, but I remember the way to the Doll House.$9#$b#I'd bet anything that's where that demon is keeping Edwin.$9",
	"NightNurseDebrief.14": "Not so fast, Mr. Rowland. Things have changed since you last had to fetch Mr. Payne.#$b#The hallways of Hell continually shift to confuse all but its native inhabitants.#$b#You may not even be able to locate Mr. Payne, never mind a suitable path through the Doll House, on your first entry.",
	"NightNurseDebrief.15": "Then we'll keep trying until we do. Right, @$9?",
	"NightNurseDebrief.16": "Very well. I hope you're prepared...",
	"NightNurseDebrief.17": "You may now enter the Doll House.",
	"NightNurseDebrief.18": "Spit spot, if you please. I cannot keep the door open forever.",

// SALOON
	// cat king 7.1 hearts - townspeople want to know him
	"catkinghearts7.1.0": "Evening, @!$h#$b#I'll be right with you.",
	"catkinghearts7.1.1": "Can I get you a drink to end the night?",
	"catkinghearts7.1.2": "No thanks.",
	"catkinghearts7.1.3": "Sigh... Always the same thing with him. I don't even know his name!$s#$b#He just comes in, hangs out in the corner, and leaves at the end of the night.$s#$b#I know he's new to town, but I thought he'd get less shy over time!",
	"catkinghearts7.1.4": "@, you know him pretty well, don't you? Do you know why he won't talk to any of us?$s",
	"catkinghearts7.1.5": "He likes to keep to himself.",
	"catkinghearts7.1.6": "It's not my place to say.",
	"catkinghearts7.1.7": "Actually, you all already know him. He's the stray cat that hangs around town sometimes.",
	"catkinghearts7.1.8": "I see... I hope he isn't too lonely.$s#$b#If you get the chance, tell him he's welcome to a chat over a drink anytime!",
	"catkinghearts7.1.9": "I understand.#$b#It might make the townspeople feel less awkward around him if he were to make some friends around town, though.",
	"catkinghearts7.1.10": "That old stray... I knew there was something odd about him!",
	"catkinghearts7.1.11": "I've fed that cat a few times... I never knew he was a cat that turns into a human.#$b#Or is he a human that turns into a cat?$s",
	"catkinghearts7.1.12": "@, I think you ought to have a talk with him. It feels like there are a lot of misunderstandings that could be cleared up...",
	
	// cat king 10 hearts - coming out to the town
	"catkinghearts10.0": "@! And you brought your friend...$h#$b#What's your name, stranger?",
	"catkinghearts10.1": "Uh... you can call me Thomas, I guess.",
	"catkinghearts10.2": "Welcome, Thomas! We're so glad to meet you.$h",
	"catkinghearts10.3": "Now, Thomas, I don't mean to be rude... but was that really you at my door the other day?",
	"catkinghearts10.4": "I'm not angry, son!#$b#Just sorry you never got that tuna I offered ye, haha!$h",
	"catkinghearts10.5": "It... doesn't bother you that I lied to you? All of you?$s",
	"catkinghearts10.6": "I'm sad you thought you needed to, but no harm done, right?#$b#Why didn't you just tell us, though?",
	"catkinghearts10.7": "I guess... it's hard, letting people in.$s#$b#I mean, I didn't even want to pay attention to @, but ${he^she^they}$ bugged me for weeks.#$b#It's ${his^her^their}$ fault I'm even here, actually.",
	"catkinghearts10.8": "@, you made me see how lonely I had made myself. I had my cats, of course, but I had hidden myself away in that cannery without even realizing.$s#$b#Even when I made a fool of myself in front of you, you didn't stop trying to befriend me.#$b#And now you've introduced me to everyone.$h#$b#So... not to be disgustingly sappy, but thank you.$l",
	"catkinghearts10.9": "I'll drink to that!$h#$b#Come here, Thomas, I'll buy the first round.#$b#Gus, put it on my tab!",
	
// SEEDSHOP
	// crystal 4 hearts - hayley is a bitch
	"crystalhearts4.0": "Oh, hi. You're... Crystal, right? Pretty name.",
	"crystalhearts4.1": "Kind of a shame that your face doesn't match...#$b#Come to me if you want a makeover, okay?",
	"crystalhearts4.2": "Sure, if I ever want to learn how to look faker than a Barbie doll, I'll let you know.$a",
	"crystalhearts4.3": "Hmph! I was just trying to help!$a",
	"crystalhearts4.4": "Oh my god, why did I say that? What the hell is wrong with me?$2",
	"crystalhearts4.6": "She deserved it.",
	"crystalhearts4.7": "That was rude. You should apologize.",
	"crystalhearts4.8": "No, she didn't deserve that...$2#$b#She just reminded me of who I don't want to be anymore.$2",
	"crystalhearts4.9": "Yeah, you're right...$2#$b#She just reminded me of who I don't want to be anymore.",
	"crystalhearts4.10": "It's a really long story, but basically, I lost all my memories a few months ago...$2#$b#I got them back eventually, but remembering that I used to be actually really shitty to a lot of people?$2#$b#It wasn't fun, let me just say that.$2#$b#I could try and make excuses for it...$s#$b#My parents were never home, I was acting out to get attention, I didn't have good role models...$s#$b#But it doesn't change the fact that I hurt a lot of people for a long time.$s",
	"crystalhearts4.11": "...Do you think I can make it up to Haley?$2",
	"crystalhearts4.12": "Do you think I can make it up to Haley?#You should apologize and take her up on the offer.#You should apologize with a gift.#You should forget about it. Neither of you meant to be rude.#You should explain to her why you reacted like that.#I'm staying out of this.",
	"crystalhearts4.13": "Okay. I'll think about it.",
	"crystalhearts4.14": "Thanks for the advice, @. I should get going.",
	
	// docks rumors
	"DocksTalks.0": "It's farmer {{PlayerName}}!",
	"DocksTalks.1": "Hello, @! I'm checking in with all the local businesses early this week. Did you hear the big news?",
	"DocksTalks.2": "The old docks east of the beach re-opened. They were shut down decades ago when the Pelican Town Port stopped bringing in any revenue.#$b#Without any income, and with municipal funds focused on interior infrastructure, they fell into disrepair and became hazardous to pedestrians.$s#$b#I've been trying to gather the funds to rejuvenate them for years!#$b#But a mysterious benefactor paid for their repair... Someone who only went by the initials 'C.K.'",
	"DocksTalks.3": "I'm hoping that increased traffic will mean more customers seeking out my fresh produce!#$b#After all, what's better than a nice, juicy orange after weeks at sea?",
	"DocksTalks.4": "I think we're all hoping for some new visitors!#$b#Between you and your farm, @, and some new maritime trade, Pelican Town could become a real hidden gem on the map!$h",
	"DocksTalks.5": "I'll probably head down there after I finish up here. If you make it over there before me, why don't you greet our mysterious new resident?",
	"DocksTalks.6": "And tell them to stop by Pierre's for the best groceries Pelican Town has to offer!$h",
	
